NAME
    gcloud beta tasks queues pause - pause a queue

SYNOPSIS
    gcloud beta tasks queues pause QUEUE [--location=LOCATION]
        [GCLOUD_WIDE_FLAG ...]

DESCRIPTION
    (BETA) If a queue is paused then the system will stop executing the tasks
    in the queue until it is resumed. Tasks can still be added when the queue
    is paused.

EXAMPLES
    To pause a queue:

        $ gcloud beta tasks queues pause my-queue

POSITIONAL ARGUMENTS
     QUEUE
        The queue to pause.

FLAGS
     --location=LOCATION
        The location where we want to manage the queue or task. If not
        specified, uses the location of the current project's App Engine app if
        there is an associated app.

GCLOUD WIDE FLAGS
    These flags are available to all commands: --access-token-file, --account,
    --billing-project, --configuration, --flags-file, --flatten, --format,
    --help, --impersonate-service-account, --log-http, --project, --quiet,
    --trace-token, --user-output-enabled, --verbosity.

    Run $ gcloud help for details.

NOTES
    This command is currently in beta and might change without notice. These
    variants are also available:

        $ gcloud tasks queues pause

        $ gcloud alpha tasks queues pause

